cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CYBER, cs.OH 

The paper discusses the usability issues of mobile spreadsheet applications, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The evaluation of the range of spreadsheet apps available for the iOS platform involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and database (cs.DB) techniques. The increasing mobile nature of business also raises cybersecurity concerns (cs.CYBER). Finally, the pilot survey conducted in the paper involves organizational behavior and human resources (cs.OH) as it examines the needs and experiences of experienced spreadsheet users.
